						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in front of the temple called <hi rend="italic">Mēlguḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Bhūlōkamalla (Sōmēśvara III).</p>						

						<p>This seems to register a gift to the god Nāgēśvara made by <hi rend="italic">Perggaḍe</hi> Dēvarasa together with the local officials of Haḷḷuhura under the instructions of <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna, Daṇḍanāyaka</hi> Sōvarasa, while <hi rend="italic">Mahāprachaṇḍa-daṇḍanāyaka</hi> Tikkapayya was governing the Two Six-hundreds. The inscription is much damaged. </p>						

						</summary>
